ce:section.ce:para:
Two experimental parts are presented in this paper. The first part aims to establish the curve for the OCV of the battery as a function of its SOC and operating temperature (
O C V − S O C − T
) using ICT data. The second part employs input data from DST and FUDS operating conditions. In the first part, the parameters of the real-time battery model are determined. This allows us to estimate the SOC and evaluate the performance of the proposed joint estimation method.
